data.title: Great Food & Service every time
data.text: Jensen's Cafe always has great food, a good selection, and friendly service every time.  We are gluten & dairy free and always have a number of options to choose from.

data.title: Great food, prices and service
data.text: We went here several times while working in the area. Very good breakfasts and dinners. The service is always quick and pleasant and the food delicious. Be prepared for a wait on the weekend mornings but they serve their own fresh brewed coffee while your waiting. They serve breakfast all day but their dinner menu is just like home cooking.

data.title: Breakfast / Brunch / Lunch Deliciousness
data.text: OMG, soooo awesome! The decisions for breakfast was difficult, to say the least... I tried the Huevos Rancheros with cheesy hashbrowns, and because I heard their Lemon Ricotta Pancakes were great, I got one on the side. Had enough for the next day's breakfast.  You will not leave hungry!

data.title: Breakfast
data.text: Best food. Amazing service! Pato is our favorite server! Strawberry and cream crepes!! Omg, so good and the Cajun breakfast with chorizo!!

data.title: Quality Slipping
data.text: Ordered eggs benedict but didn't realize that to get traditional style you had to specify on an Eng. Muffin or it comes on a pancake.  The worst Hollandaise sauce ever.  I'll avoid that - if I ever go back.  Over priced and quality is slipping.

data.title: We hoped for better, but service and some food was just average
data.text: The Jensen Cafe reminded us of the First Watch chain, and our meals were served hot. Unfortunately, the sandwich for my wife was a bit tough, and my toast similar. My eggs were hot, which was nice. Service was only average, with few offers to refill our drinks. If we visit Burnsville again, we probably would look for other options.

data.title: Great breakfast
data.text: Was recommended by the hotel I was staying at to eat here. Great place for breakfast and coffee. The food was awesome and we could sit outside. The patio area was very nice.  Small cafe that is perfect for hanging out and conversing with friends. The service was great and I would highly recommend this place to anyone!!

data.title: Good Food, Not Great for Large Groups
data.text: We recently visited Jensen's Cafe for my mom's birthday. There were seven of us, and the seating was cramped. The food, however, was good, and the service was friendly. The coffee was good and strong!

data.title: Lovely Surprise!
data.text: Where do you choose to meet your son's girlfriend for the very first time?  That's right, just she and I, lunch together, never having met before.  We both came 4 hours from opposite directions and met in the middle.  She did the choosing -Jensen's Cafe - based upon an Internet search.  SMART GIRL.  FABULOUS RESTAURANT.  I can't say enough positive things about this place.  The service is matchless; the food is light, fresh, unique and delish; the facility has plenty of natural light and a high ceiling but it didn't feel oppressive (you know how sometimes the sun can bear down through a restaurant window and make the whole meal uncomfortable...). I ordered the Salmon Eggs Benedict and was surprised when it arrived on little pancakes and not English muffins (apparently I didn't read the menu well as I was concentrating more on "the girl").  It was scrumptious. I savored every bite.  The pancake was not sweet or distracting, only delicate and quite a special complement to the dish.  And then she and I shared Swedish Pancakes with Strawberries and Cream for dessert.  Let me say this, from a girl who grew up making Swedish pancakes with her Swedish grandmama, these are the real deal.  I just about cried; yes, just like grandma and I used to make, including the larger size, light brown with bubbly marks AND the crispy edges.  Unbelievable.  I thought, "this deserves a cup of tea alongside," so I ordered Earl Gray.  The waiter brought a clean, shining, quality mug and saucer, teapot with extra water and a very special tea bag like I had never seen before.  It didn't have a string and tag; it was the normal width but twice as long. So easy to handle!  Is this a "cafe"? Really?  Don't let that word communicate anything but refreshing goodness to you.  I wouldn't call it a "cafe".  Pretty furniture, pretty environs, pretty food, not "foo-foo," just pretty.  Everything about this restaurant is a pleasant experience. And A+ for service.  Anyway, "the girl" and I have started out on the right foot. I approve.  She's a keeper, son.  Don't let this one slip through your fingers!!

data.title: Breakfast from years gone by!
data.text: This is a great local cafe, with long-time, steady staff and consistently excellent customer service.  The restaurant feels like a local cafe of previous times where people met to have an unrushed meal and greet others they knew who were also dining there.  The menu has many unique items, such as some Tex-Mex omelets and Scandinavian pancakes, as well as traditional breakfasts.  Food is well-prepared, with generous but not excessive portions.  I would recommend their Scandinavian menu items, as it is hard to find a comparable in quality anywhere else.

data.title: It was decent
data.text: I've been to Jensens 4 times in the past couple of years and it seems like the food quality has consistently gone down since my first visit. It is always so busy so I don't think I will go again due to my last two meals being cooked "ok." However, The staff are always friendly and the establishment is tidy so that's a plus.

data.title: Great Homemade Syrup for Pancakes!
data.text: The pancakes were amazing.  Great tasting buttermilk pancakes but the warm homemade syrup tasted like the carmel on homemade rolls.   The burgers were very good as were the cafe potatoes and cheesy hashbrowns.  The omelet was only OK. The service was excellent except for the fact that they overcharged us.

data.title: Excellent breakfast
data.text: Jensen's is a great place for breakfast. the steel cut oats are very good, and they have traditional breakfasts that are better than most. The ambiance is casual and clean. Prices are reasonable.

data.title: Fantastic Breakfast!
data.text:
I visited Jensen's for breakfast, and well, I can only say that the food is simply delicious. I tried the Bacon Benedict, with a couple of pancakes on the side, they are subtly fantastic, fresh OJ, fresh coffee and the Butter Maple Syrup is amazing. 

Great service and relaxing atmosphere.

data.title: Confortable!
data.text: A great locat cafe which features Scandinavian Specialties and even has a Tex-Mex menu as well.  Located in the heart of Burnsville and a good place for any meal.

data.title: This is definitely 'Just Okay'
data.text: This is a very popular breakfast place, however, it actually is overpriced and has average food. Today, the cheesy hash browns seemed quite greasy and overcooked. The waitress seems to have fun filling our coffee cups to the absolute brim, making it almost impossible to pick up without spilling.  Also, seems like the wait staff is constantly trying to upsell something that "costs just $1.00 more."  By the end of it, you've got a $15.00 breakfast. All of the omelets have 4 eggs - which is just too much food. I've been here many times and always leave feeling a bit let down.

data.title: Weekend in the Twin Cities
data.text: This is a great little restaurant but be prepared to have a little wait.  This is a local favorite and it is always busy but for a good reason the food is awesome.  When we come we take home a pint of there home made syrup.  You can't go wrong eating here.

data.title: Most tasty breakfast
data.text: Nice cafe atmosphere.  Clean, bright good service and wonderful food.  If you live around here you should be frequenting this place often.  Then go shopping at Ficus and Fig next door to complete your adventure.

data.title: Great food.
data.text: I love this place, eat there regularly. I've  never had a bad meal there, ever. Outside seating during the summer too.

data.title: Best for Breakfast!
data.text: If you are looking for a breakfast that satisfies, this is the place to go.  No matter what you order, it is piping hot, tasty and sure to please.  The pancakes, waffles, eggs, bacon and cheesy potatoes are all top drawer.  The Swedish pancakes served with lingonberries are not often found on menus; the syrup and jam are homemade and the "kiddie" chocolate chip pancakes are a winner.  They also have several egg dishes with a Mexican flair.  You can't go wrong getting a breakfast at Jensen's.
